Canadian Freedom Waves to Gaza organizers say activists on the Canadian ship Tahrir that, along with the Irish MV Saoirse, who were headed to the Gaza Strip, were intercepted by Israeli troops. The activists refused to voluntarily leave the ship; Israel says no one was hurt.(The Globe and Mail) (CBC) (Salem-News.com) (Jerusalem Post) (Ynetnews.com)Demonstrators against the regime flood a main highway in a march stretching for miles as Bahrain's rulers struggle to contain opposition anger ahead of the Formula 1 Grand Prix. (The Daily Telegraph)